About
This airy, outdoor village-styled center is a must-see, must-shop for shoppers. Las Vegas North Premium Outlets® features over 175 designer and name-brand retailers offering savings up to 65% every day including kate spade new york, Michael Kors, Pandora, Tory Burch, Coach, Brooks Brothers Factory Outlet and many more. Enjoy dining at The Cheesecake Factory, Shake Shack, Chipotle or our fabulous Food Court. The center is conveniently located just minutes from the heart of the Strip; off I-15 at Exit 41 - Charleston Boulevard and is serviced by taxis, ride share and the public bus.
Duration: 2-3 hours

    Best Outlets in Las Vegas!
    The North Premium Outlets is absolutely amazing! It's a very popular shopping destination for locals and tourists, only a few miles North of the Las Vegas Strip. I've been going there for over 15 years and always find the best deals. There's over 175 stores from casual to luxury brands. There's also many food options available such as Chipotle, Shake Shack, The Cheesecake factory, and a food court. If you visit their website sign up for their VIP shopper Club to receive rewards, discounts, and exclusive offers. Free parking for locals w/ Nevada ID!

  • big_phil2010

    Great Prices
    I was glad we brought a spare suitcase on holiday to load up with all the great bargains we picked up whilst shopping here. We found that most shops actually sold items for less than what they were displayed at, only to then get even more discounts at checkout by leaving your email. Saved a fortune on most of our purchases. The Wi-Fi was a bit patchy, so I’d recommend downloading the Simon Premium Outlets app from the App Store before you go, as this lets you get even more bargains at some shops, such as Michael Kors. This place is a taxi ride from the stripe, but well worth it. Only improvement for me would be to have more shade to save you for the relentless Vegas sun.

The Outlet mall are so close to the County building that perhaps that may be the best link. The "Other" and perhaps larger Outlet mall (Indoors) lies west of the Airport, so for me, it's a toss up as to what my after the shop intentions are for free entertainment, I prefer the downtown area with their Freemont Experience. For you? A very sincere....ENJOY !!
